And this is total

00:36:51.626 --> 00:36:52.960
theoretical framework here.

00:36:52.960 --> 00:36:54.420
So it's like you never really know.

00:36:54.420 --> 00:36:55.296
But you see

00:36:55.296 --> 00:36:58.216
what you can do with this or

00:36:58.216 --> 00:37:01.469
the key is nuclear power or something.

00:37:01.469 --> 00:37:02.803
And it's like the gorilla has

00:37:02.803 --> 00:37:03.679
we have the key.

00:37:03.679 --> 00:37:05.223
Another analogy

00:37:05.223 --> 00:37:07.225
that Eric Weinstein loves to use

00:37:07.225 --> 00:37:09.227
is he talks about

00:37:09.227 --> 00:37:10.686
North Sentinel Island,

00:37:10.686 --> 00:37:11.437
which is

00:37:11.437 --> 00:37:12.813
an island of Aboriginals

00:37:12.813 --> 00:37:15.191
who basically have not made any contact

00:37:15.191 --> 00:37:16.359
with with civilization.

00:37:16.359 --> 00:37:17.818
It's off the coast of India,

00:37:17.818 --> 00:37:19.028
and the Indian government basically

00:37:19.028 --> 00:37:20.112
just lets them do their thing

00:37:20.112 --> 00:37:21.155
and kind of respects them.

00:37:21.155 --> 00:37:23.199
And take this analogy,

00:37:23.199 --> 00:37:24.158
if the North Sentinelese

00:37:24.158 --> 00:37:26.410
started developing nukes,

00:37:26.410 --> 00:37:27.912
maybe the Indian government

00:37:27.912 --> 00:37:28.579
