00:38:34.061 --> 00:38:35.146
would cause somebody

00:38:35.146 --> 00:38:37.231
to even make sort of contact.

00:38:37.231 --> 00:38:37.732
But do you have

00:38:37.732 --> 00:38:38.774
do we have any theories

00:38:38.774 --> 00:38:39.442
on kind of

00:38:39.442 --> 00:38:40.443
the electromagnetic

00:38:40.443 --> 00:38:40.860
radiation component?

00:38:40.860 --> 00:38:43.946
I mean, I mean, certainly if we were to

00:38:44.113 --> 00:38:44.530
look at it

00:38:44.530 --> 00:38:44.905
from like

00:38:44.905 --> 00:38:46.866
a relativistic perspective,

00:38:46.866 --> 00:38:48.451
well, that sounds like visible band

00:38:48.451 --> 00:38:49.493
light being blue

00:38:49.493 --> 00:38:51.245
shifted into the ultraviolet

00:38:51.245 --> 00:38:53.414
and you're getting literally a sunburn.

00:38:53.414 --> 00:38:56.375
And and if you look at an Alcubierre

00:38:56.375 --> 00:38:58.336
type thing where, you know,

00:38:58.336 --> 00:38:59.295
lights getting lensed

00:38:59.295 --> 00:39:00.796
around the craft, etc., stuff

00:39:00.796 --> 00:39:02.923
