00:39:02.923 --> 00:39:04.508
So things coming towards

00:39:04.508 --> 00:39:06.510
you would actually redshift spectrally.

00:39:06.510 --> 00:39:09.221
And the people getting like burns

00:39:09.221 --> 00:39:10.389
so that's ultraviolet

00:39:10.389 --> 00:39:12.308
it's like ionizing radiation.

00:39:12.308 --> 00:39:14.477
So that would be light

00:39:14.477 --> 00:39:16.979
being blue shifted into the ultraviolet

00:39:16.979 --> 00:39:18.856
as it's lens

00:39:18.856 --> 00:39:20.024
across the bubble

00:39:20.024 --> 00:39:21.525
that the craft creates.

00:39:21.525 --> 00:39:24.528
And so we are seeing artifacts

00:39:24.528 --> 00:39:26.781
that seem to show that it's

00:39:26.781 --> 00:39:27.406
they're basically

00:39:27.406 --> 00:39:29.325
manipulating space time.

00:39:29.325 --> 00:39:30.326
And I guess that's

00:39:30.326 --> 00:39:31.410
why you get this sort

00:39:31.410 --> 00:39:33.329
of skipping across

00:39:33.329 --> 00:39:34.830
time effect or something.

00:39:34.830 --> 00:39:37.166
It looks like the things are just

00:39:37.166 --> 00:39:37.750
you're sort of you're

00:39:37.750 --> 00:39:38.918
literally folding space

00:39:38.918 --> 00:39:39.668
time, I guess, so

00:39:39.668 --> 00:39:40.544
you can get from point A

00:39:40.544 --> 00:39:42.088
to point Z- you're riding a wave,

00:39:42.088 --> 00:39:43.839
basically create a wave

00:39:43.839 --> 00:39:46.092
and you're on top of the tsunami wave

00:39:46.092 --> 00:39:49.595
and you're riding across space time.

00:39:49.678 --> 00:39:50.846
And then, of course, there's

00:39:50.846 --> 00:39:51.972
the kind of the other thing

00:39:51.972 --> 00:39:52.515
is, you know, if

00:39:52.515 --> 00:39:53.265
it's like an Einstein

00:39:53.265 --> 00:39:54.683
Rosen Bridge thing,

00:39:54.683 --> 00:39:55.476
you know, two points

00:39:55.476 --> 00:39:57.853
on a piece of paper and you fold it.

00:39:57.853 --> 00:39:58.813
But like

00:39:58.813 --> 00:39:59.438
but the way

00:39:59.438 --> 00:40:02.566
they're jumping around and skipping is

00:40:02.566 --> 00:40:03.734
if you're riding the wave,

00:40:03.734 --> 00:40:05.069
it looks like you're moving

00:40:05.069 --> 00:40:08.155
very rapidly and

00:40:08.322 --> 00:40:09.698
like punctuated

00:40:09.698 --> 00:40:10.699
kind of movements

00:40:10.699 --> 00:40:13.077
because think of an accordion

00:40:13.077 --> 00:40:14.453
and those waves, the wave

00:40:14.453 --> 00:40:15.162
you’re riding’s an accordion,

00:40:15.162 --> 00:40:16.497
when you flatten out the accordion

00:40:16.497 --> 00:40:18.249
like flat space time,

00:40:18.249 --> 00:40:20.126
you would smoothly move across.

00:40:20.126 --> 00:40:21.836
But I think we're we're stuck

00:40:21.836 --> 00:40:22.837
with like, Einstein’s

00:40:22.837 --> 00:40:25.965
stuff was amazing and nobody's really

00:40:25.965 --> 00:40:26.298
I mean, there's

00:40:26.298 --> 00:40:29.427
obviously people with string theory,

00:40:29.427 --> 00:40:30.302
M brane,

00:40:30.302 --> 00:40:31.679
all these other different

00:40:31.679 --> 00:40:32.763
physics theories, you know,

00:40:32.763 --> 00:40:35.141
quantum gravity and other theories.

00:40:35.141 --> 00:40:35.850
But, you know,

00:40:35.850 --> 00:40:36.642
there hasn't been something

00:40:36.642 --> 00:40:37.268
that's, you know,

00:40:37.268 --> 00:40:39.562
unified all the weak and strong

00:40:39.562 --> 00:40:40.604
force, etc..

00:40:40.604 --> 00:40:42.731
And that's an ongoing thing.

00:40:42.731 --> 00:40:43.858
And I think you finding the Higgs

00:40:43.858 --> 00:40:45.609
boson is going to be the big answer.

00:40:45.609 --> 00:40:46.527
Yeah, we'll see.

00:40:46.527 --> 00:40:48.362
So speaking of string theory,

00:40:48.362 --> 00:40:49.613
it feels like it

00:40:49.613 --> 00:40:51.157
just hasn't shipped a product.

00:40:51.157 --> 00:40:52.741
You have our best and brightest,

00:40:52.741 --> 00:40:54.910
often really smart people

00:40:54.910 --> 00:40:57.538
getting into this sort of field that,

00:40:57.538 --> 00:40:59.165
you know,
maybe you can detect black holes

