with strings,

00:40:59.707 --> 00:41:00.833
but generally it's

00:41:00.833 --> 00:41:02.084
just not that useful.

00:41:02.084 --> 00:41:03.252
Well, string theory,

00:41:03.252 --> 00:41:05.754
I mean, mathematically

00:41:05.796 --> 00:41:07.131
it works out right?

00:41:07.131 --> 00:41:08.007
But like

00:41:08.007 --> 00:41:08.883
most of the stuff

00:41:08.883 --> 00:41:10.843
you can't empirically observe

00:41:10.843 --> 00:41:12.678
because the strings are so small.

00:41:12.678 --> 00:41:14.430
Subatomically there's just like,

00:41:14.430 --> 00:41:16.557
no way of- it’s 11 dimensions.

00:41:16.557 --> 00:41:18.517
No way of verifying that.

00:41:18.517 --> 00:41:20.019
So it's a nice

00:41:20.019 --> 00:41:22.438
I'll call it like overlay or that

00:41:22.438 --> 00:41:23.355
that maybe this,

00:41:23.355 --> 00:41:25.441
maybe this is reality maybe it's not,

00:41:25.441 --> 00:41:26.400
it mathematically works out.

00:41:26.400 --> 00:41:28.611
I think it's force fitting

00:41:28.611 --> 00:41:29.737
general relativity

00:41:29.737 --> 00:41:31.280
and quantum field theory.

00:41:31.280 --> 00:41:32.490
But this brings

00:41:32.490 --> 00:41:33.616
up an interesting question, which is

00:41:33.616 --> 00:41:34.909
can we go down the tree

00:41:34.909 --> 00:41:35.951
trunk of physics

00:41:35.951 --> 00:41:38.954
and then find another branch?

00:41:38.954 --> 00:41:41.415
Clearly quantum physics with nuclear

00:41:41.415 --> 00:41:42.583
and hydrogen bombs

00:41:42.583 --> 00:41:43.876
as its byproducts

00:41:43.876 --> 00:41:45.878
was becoming dangerous.

00:41:45.878 --> 00:41:47.505
It is an atomic bomb.

00:41:47.505 --> 00:41:49.757
It is a harnessing of the basic power

00:41:49.757 --> 00:41:51.383
of the universe.

00:41:51.383 --> 00:41:52.426
After the invention

00:41:52.426 --> 00:41:54.970
of these apocalyptic weapons was true

00:41:54.970 --> 00:41:56.263
fundamental physics

00:41:56.263 --> 00:41:57.681
then concealed in deep

00:41:57.681 --> 00:41:59.058
black aerospace?

00:41:59.058 --> 00:42:00.643
While public facing physics,

00:42:00.643 --> 00:42:02.228
was sent into a cul de sac

00:42:02.228 --> 00:42:04.146
so it could do less damage?

00:42:05.731 --> 00:42:07.942
Were there actually updates in physics,

00:42:07.942 --> 00:42:09.485
maybe mid-century,

00:42:09.485 --> 00:42:12.321
that were not disclosed to the public?

00:42:14.114 --> 00:42:15.574
Okay, I realize this sounds

00:42:15.574 --> 00:42:17.576
kind of insane, but hear me out.

00:42:17.576 --> 00:42:18.244
Imagine that

00:42:18.244 --> 00:42:20.079
this billiard ball is a proton.

00:42:20.079 --> 00:42:21.997
The golden age of relativity,

00:42:21.997 --> 00:42:23.040
was a wild,

00:42:23.040 --> 00:42:24.041
forgotten time

00:42:24.041 --> 00:42:26.293
in the history of American physics.

00:42:26.293 --> 00:42:28.128
This was a period in the fifties

00:42:28.128 --> 00:42:30.047
where the study of antigravity-

00:42:30.047 --> 00:42:32.258
Yeah, you heard me right, antigravity.

00:42:32.258 --> 00:42:33.884
Experienced a dramatic

00:42:33.884 --> 00:42:35.469
resurgence of interest,

00:42:35.469 --> 00:42:37.096
not just among quacks,

00:42:37.096 --> 00:42:38.806
among real physicists.

00:42:38.806 --> 00:42:39.348
Since then,

00:42:39.348 --> 00:42:40.891
there has been a steady

00:42:40.891 --> 00:42:42.560
but constant improvement.

00:42:42.560 --> 00:42:43.686
Roger Babson,

00:42:43.686 --> 00:42:46.146
a patron of science, was obsessed

00:42:46.146 --> 00:42:47.231
with finding the solution

00:42:47.231 --> 00:42:48.148
to antigravity.

00:42:48.148 --> 00:42:50.025
His Gravity Research Foundation

00:42:50.025 --> 00:42:51.944
held a popular essay contest

00:42:51.944 --> 00:42:53.571
which garnered contributions

00:42:53.571 --> 00:42:55.823
from many of the top minds at the time.

00:42:55.823 --> 00:42:57.741
Meanwhile, another industrialist,

00:42:57.741 --> 00:42:58.951
Agnew Bahnson,

00:42:58.951 --> 00:43:00.953
started the Institute of Field Physics

00:43:00.953 --> 00:43:02.079
in North Carolina,

00:43:02.079 --> 00:43:04.790
also dedicated to study of antigravity.

00:43:04.790 --> 00:43:06.250
His Chapel Hill conference

00:43:06.250 --> 00:43:08.252
in 1957 included

00:43:08.252 --> 00:43:10.504
top physicists like Bryce DeWitt,

00:43:10.504 --> 00:43:12.673
Richard Feynman, Peter Bergman,

00:43:12.673 --> 00:43:14.675
Freeman Dyson and John Wheeler

00:43:14.675 --> 00:43:15.968
all there to discuss

00:43:15.968 --> 00:43:18.012
the role of gravity in physics.

00:43:18.012 --> 00:43:18.887
As physicist

00:43:18.887 --> 00:43:20.598
Louis Witten would go on to say

00:43:20.598 --> 00:43:22.516
about antigravity in the fifties,

00:43:22.516 --> 00:43:23.809
it was in the wind,

00:43:23.809 --> 00:43:25.352
meaning it was everywhere.

00:43:25.352 --> 00:43:25.728
He said,

00:43:25.728 --> 00:43:27.646
What are you doing about anti-gravity?

00:43:27.646 --> 00:43:28.731
And I said, Well, I'm

00:43:28.731 --> 00:43:30.649
not against gravity.

00:43:34.695 --> 00:43:36.530
Witten actually worked in Martin

00:43:36.530 --> 00:43:38.073
Corporation's Antigravity

00:43:38.073 --> 00:43:39.742
Research unit. That's right.

00:43:39.742 --> 00:43:41.035
They had an antigravity

00:43:41.035 --> 00:43:42.161
research outfit.

00:43:42.161 --> 00:43:43.996
It was called Research Institute

00:43:43.996 --> 00:43:45.164
for Advanced Studies,

00:43:45.164 --> 00:43:47.082
or RIAS for short.

00:43:47.082 --> 00:43:48.375
And Martin Corporation,

00:43:48.375 --> 00:43:49.585
of course, would later

00:43:49.585 --> 00:43:50.919
become Lockheed Martin.

00:43:50.919 --> 00:43:51.754
Louis Witten's

00:43:51.754 --> 00:43:52.796
direct boss

00:43:52.796 --> 00:43:55.883
at RIAS was a guy named George Trimble

00:43:56.050 --> 00:43:57.926
in a 1956 article

00:43:57.926 --> 00:43:59.887
found in Jane's Defense Weekly.

00:43:59.887 --> 00:44:00.763
George Trimble

00:44:00.763 --> 00:44:01.805
said, We're already

00:44:01.805 --> 00:44:03.015
working on nuclear

00:44:03.015 --> 00:44:04.183
fuels and equipment

00:44:04.183 --> 00:44:04.933
to cancel out

00:44:04.933 --> 00:44:06.185
gravity, and added

00:44:06.185 --> 00:44:07.645
that the conquest of gravity

00:44:07.645 --> 00:44:08.354
could be done

00:44:08.354 --> 00:44:09.813
in about the amount of time

00:44:09.813 --> 00:44:12.024
it took to build the first atom bomb.

00:44:12.024 --> 00:44:12.775
By the time

00:44:12.775 --> 00:44:14.068
the sixties had rolled around,

00:44:14.068 --> 00:44:15.736
most people had kind of forgotten

00:44:15.736 --> 00:44:16.862
about antigravity.

00:44:16.862 --> 00:44:17.780
It quieted down

00:44:17.780 --> 00:44:19.657
because nobody ever got anywhere,

00:44:19.657 --> 00:44:20.824
or it quieted down

00:44:20.824 --> 00:44:21.575
because it did get

00:44:21.575 --> 00:44:24.119
somewhere and it went black.

00:44:24.203 --> 00:44:25.579
This kind of weird where,

00:44:25.579 --> 00:44:26.789
as far as I know,

00:44:26.789 --> 00:44:27.790
in my kind of

00:44:27.790 --> 00:44:29.041
topological physics

00:44:29.041 --> 00:44:31.377
history knowledge, where,

00:44:31.377 --> 00:44:33.962
you know,
there was all these anti-grav groups

00:44:33.962 --> 00:44:35.339
up until the early sixties

00:44:35.339 --> 00:44:36.757
and then they, you know,

00:44:36.757 --> 00:44:38.050
totally vaporized.

00:44:38.050 --> 00:44:39.385
You know,

00:44:39.385 --> 00:44:40.719
there's physics knowledge

00:44:40.719 --> 00:44:42.471
held by aerospace companies

00:44:42.471 --> 00:44:43.055
that is not known.

00:44:43.055 --> 00:44:44.765
There certainly is materials knowledge.

00:44:44.765 --> 00:44:47.976
Materials which involves

00:44:47.976 --> 00:44:50.187
topological physics or whatever.

00:44:50.187 --> 00:44:51.105
It's hard to say

00:44:51.105 --> 00:44:52.815
whether anything real was discovered

00:44:52.815 --> 00:44:54.316
in the realm of anti-gravity

00:44:54.316 --> 00:44:55.567
or if it went black.

00:44:55.567 --> 00:44:57.319
But when aviation journalist,

00:44:57.319 --> 00:44:59.279
Nick Cook, tried to meet with the

00:44:59.279 --> 00:45:00.823
then long retired 80

00:45:00.823 --> 00:45:02.449
something year old George Trimble

00:45:02.449 --> 00:45:03.909
through a friend of his at Lockheed

00:45:03.909 --> 00:45:05.536
Martin, this was the message

00:45:05.536 --> 00:45:08.038
he received back: Quote, unquote-

00:45:08.038 --> 00:45:09.707
I don't know who this old man

00:45:09.707 --> 00:45:12.042
is or what he once was,

00:45:12.042 --> 00:45:14.336
but he told me in no uncertain terms

00:45:14.336 --> 00:45:15.838
to get off his case.

00:45:15.838 --> 00:45:17.297
He doesn't want to speak to me

00:45:17.297 --> 00:45:18.924
and he doesn't want to speak to you.

00:45:18.924 --> 00:45:20.843
Not now, not ever.

00:45:20.843 --> 00:45:22.094
I don't mind telling you

00:45:22.094 --> 00:45:24.054
that he sounded scared.

00:45:24.054 --> 00:45:25.723
Did deep black Aerospace

00:45:25.723 --> 00:45:27.599
secretly make a huge breakthrough

00:45:27.599 --> 00:45:28.600
in antigravity?

00:45:28.600 --> 00:45:30.102
Well, when he worked for Martin

00:45:30.102 --> 00:45:30.936
in the fifties,

00:45:30.936 --> 00:45:31.603
Lewis Witten

00:45:31.603 --> 00:45:33.313
specialized in nonlinear

00:45:33.313 --> 00:45:35.315
algebra and topological physics.

00:45:35.315 --> 00:45:36.900
The two things that you'd need

00:45:36.900 --> 00:45:38.235
to investigate gravity

00:45:38.235 --> 00:45:40.612
and maybe how to beat it.

00:45:40.612 --> 00:45:41.905
He also did contract

00:45:41.905 --> 00:45:42.740
work on gravity

00:45:42.740 --> 00:45:45.242
for Wright-Patterson Air Force Base.

00:45:45.242 --> 00:45:47.202
The reason there was a laboratory

00:45:47.202 --> 00:45:47.619
at Wright

00:45:47.619 --> 00:45:49.580
Field was to find out

00:45:49.580 --> 00:45:50.706
what we were doing

00:45:50.706 --> 00:45:52.374
and to help us do it.

00:45:52.374 --> 00:45:54.126
And I got a contract from Wright

00:45:54.126 --> 00:45:55.961
Field to do it,

00:45:55.961 --> 00:45:57.296
to do Gravity,

00:45:57.296 --> 00:45:59.673
which I did very happily.

00:45:59.673 --> 00:46:01.550
And who is Louis Witten’s son?

00:46:01.550 --> 00:46:02.593
Ed Witten.

00:46:02.593 --> 00:46:04.219
Just the most formidable

00:46:04.219 --> 00:46:05.721
proponent of string theory,

00:46:05.721 --> 00:46:06.972
maybe of all time.

00:46:06.972 --> 00:46:08.891
Do you think that string theory,

00:46:08.891 --> 00:46:10.058
which Ed Witten worked

00:46:10.058 --> 00:46:11.351
on, is intentionally

00:46:11.351 --> 00:46:13.061
a bridge to nowhere?

00:46:13.061 --> 00:46:14.772
I have privately said to you

00:46:14.772 --> 00:46:16.940
that string theory was a

00:46:16.940 --> 00:46:18.692
very odd development

00:46:18.692 --> 00:46:20.861
because it both allowed physics

00:46:20.861 --> 00:46:21.820
to proceed

00:46:21.820 --> 00:46:24.364
as if it was doing something new

00:46:24.364 --> 00:46:26.325
while breaking no new ground

00:46:26.325 --> 00:46:28.994
in the physical world in which we live.

00:46:29.953 --> 00:46:30.662
I don't really

00:46:30.662 --> 00:46:31.538
know if you were trying

00:46:31.538 --> 00:46:33.832
to stagnate the field,

00:46:33.832 --> 00:46:37.795
string theory is pretty brilliant.

00:46:37.836 --> 00:46:39.087
And remember that Chapel

00:46:39.087 --> 00:46:40.380
Hill conference that’s thrown

00:46:40.380 --> 00:46:43.592
in 1957 by Agnew Bahnson who's obsessed

00:46:43.592 --> 00:46:44.802
with antigravity?

00:46:44.802 --> 00:46:46.845
Well, Louis Witten was there.

00:46:46.845 --> 00:46:47.971
And the conference helped

00:46:47.971 --> 00:46:49.765
establish quantum gravity

00:46:49.765 --> 00:46:52.309
of which string theory is an offshoot.

00:46:52.309 --> 00:46:53.018
In an interview

00:46:53.018 --> 00:46:54.978
with the American Institute of Physics,

00:46:54.978 --> 00:46:56.563
when antigravity gets brought

00:46:56.563 --> 00:46:58.482
up, Louis Witten says,

00:46:58.482 --> 00:47:00.442
a guy named Townsend discovered

00:47:00.442 --> 00:47:02.027
that there was a type of bismuth

00:47:02.027 --> 00:47:03.111
that was repelled

00:47:03.111 --> 00:47:04.363
instead of attracting.

00:47:04.363 --> 00:47:06.031
There was a vice president

00:47:06.031 --> 00:47:07.115
of the Martin Company

00:47:07.115 --> 00:47:07.991
who brought that up.

00:47:07.991 --> 00:47:10.452
He said, I read about a guy in Indiana

00:47:10.452 --> 00:47:12.579
who says the rock of bismuth, that's

00:47:12.579 --> 00:47:14.623
it shows antigravity.

00:47:14.623 --> 00:47:16.792
And where have we heard about bismuth

00:47:16.792 --> 00:47:17.584
with possible

00:47:17.584 --> 00:47:19.461
anti-gravity properties before?

00:47:19.461 --> 00:47:20.170
That's Gary

00:47:20.170 --> 00:47:22.256
Nolan, Stanford microbiologist

00:47:22.256 --> 00:47:23.465
and Nobel nominee

00:47:23.465 --> 00:47:26.051
who claims to have UFO crash parts

00:47:26.051 --> 00:47:27.719
with isotope ratios

00:47:27.719 --> 00:47:29.972
that don't occur naturally on earth.

00:47:29.972 --> 00:47:30.931
One of his pieces

00:47:30.931 --> 00:47:32.057
that we looked at together

00:47:32.057 --> 00:47:34.935
when I visited was magnesium bismuth.

00:47:34.935 --> 00:47:36.478
Bismuth layers,

00:47:36.478 --> 00:47:37.813
less than a human hair

00:47:37.813 --> 00:47:39.356
supposedly picked up

00:47:39.356 --> 00:47:40.691
in the crash retrieval

00:47:40.691 --> 00:47:43.318
of an advanced aerospace vehicle.

00:47:43.318 --> 00:47:44.987
Nowhere could we find any evidence

00:47:44.987 --> 00:47:46.572
that anybody ever made one of these.

00:47:46.572 --> 00:47:47.948
And who's this Townsend

00:47:47.948 --> 00:47:49.741
guy Witten’s referring to?

00:47:49.741 --> 00:47:51.368
Witten had to have been talking

00:47:51.368 --> 00:47:52.786
about Townsend Brown,

00:47:52.786 --> 00:47:54.162
one of the country's leading

00:47:54.162 --> 00:47:56.540
antigravity researchers at the time.

00:48:02.004 --> 00:48:02.504
Yeah, and there's a

00:48:02.504 --> 00:48:03.338
guy named Townsend

00:48:03.338 --> 00:48:06.508
Brown who had a theory that if you took

00:48:06.508 --> 00:48:07.509
two charged plates

00:48:07.509 --> 00:48:08.385
and then you put something

00:48:08.385 --> 00:48:09.803
neutral between them,

00:48:09.803 --> 00:48:10.596
the neutral thing would

00:48:10.596 --> 00:48:12.431
sort of gravitate a little towards

00:48:12.431 --> 00:48:14.558
the positively charged plate.

00:48:14.558 --> 00:48:15.934
And you could basically

00:48:15.934 --> 00:48:17.060
figure out antigravity.

00:48:17.060 --> 00:48:18.270
From the outside,

00:48:18.270 --> 00:48:19.563
Townsend Brown sort of

00:48:19.563 --> 00:48:21.064
looks like an amateurish

00:48:21.064 --> 00:48:22.482
mid-century physicist

00:48:22.482 --> 00:48:23.775
and failed inventor

00:48:23.775 --> 00:48:24.943
exploring the kooky

00:48:24.943 --> 00:48:26.361
world of antigravity

00:48:26.361 --> 00:48:27.988
just to end up failing in

00:48:27.988 --> 00:48:29.740
creating the intellectual property

00:48:29.740 --> 00:48:32.326
behind the Ionic Breeze Air Purifier.

00:48:32.326 --> 00:48:33.577
I'm not joking.

00:48:33.577 --> 00:48:35.245
But a great biography called

00:48:35.245 --> 00:48:35.704
The Man

00:48:35.704 --> 00:48:37.497
Who Mastered Gravity by Paul

00:48:37.497 --> 00:48:39.791
Schatzkin tells the real story.

00:48:39.791 --> 00:48:40.959
He parachuted

00:48:40.959 --> 00:48:45.088
behind enemy lines into Germany in 1944

00:48:45.172 --> 00:48:48.926
and started looking into the German

00:48:48.926 --> 00:48:51.261
UFO reverse engineering program.

00:48:51.261 --> 00:48:53.764
That’s crazy.

00:48:53.764 --> 00:48:56.808
OSS and MI6 super spies Bill Donovan

00:48:56.808 --> 00:48:57.309
and William

00:48:57.309 --> 00:48:58.101
Stephenson

00:48:58.101 --> 00:48:59.770
needed the Allies preeminent

00:48:59.770 --> 00:49:01.146
antigravity scientist

00:49:01.146 --> 00:49:03.190
to investigate the notorious Foo

00:49:03.190 --> 00:49:04.524
Fighter phenomena.

00:49:04.524 --> 00:49:06.234
These were bizarre orbs

00:49:06.234 --> 00:49:06.902
that looked like

00:49:06.902 --> 00:49:08.570
intelligently controlled ball

00:49:08.570 --> 00:49:10.489
lightning popping up all over

00:49:10.489 --> 00:49:11.990
Germany in the early forties

00:49:11.990 --> 00:49:14.743
and messing with Allied fighter pilots.

00:49:17.829 --> 00:49:18.830
I couldn't find a

00:49:18.830 --> 00:49:20.040
ton of corroboration

00:49:20.040 --> 00:49:21.249
outside of Schatzkin’s

00:49:21.249 --> 00:49:22.709
book on this story.

00:49:22.709 --> 00:49:24.503
But here's why I think it's true.

00:49:24.503 --> 00:49:25.879
We do know for a fact

00:49:25.879 --> 00:49:27.130
that Eisenhower sent

00:49:27.130 --> 00:49:28.173
General James

00:49:28.173 --> 00:49:29.633
Doolittle to investigate

00:49:29.633 --> 00:49:31.385
Swedish ghost rockets.

00:49:31.385 --> 00:49:33.220
These were tons of UFO sightings

00:49:33.220 --> 00:49:33.845
in Sweden

00:49:33.845 --> 00:49:35.222
and Finland in the immediate

00:49:35.222 --> 00:49:37.099
aftermath of World War II.

00:49:37.099 --> 00:49:38.433
Curiously, Doolittle

00:49:38.433 --> 00:49:40.268
then went back to the United States

00:49:40.268 --> 00:49:41.770
just to found the Lindbergh

00:49:41.770 --> 00:49:43.605
Foundation, which researched

00:49:43.605 --> 00:49:45.941
novel aviation propulsion methods.

00:49:45.941 --> 00:49:47.442
So I wouldn't be totally surprised

00:49:47.442 --> 00:49:48.860
if Townsend Brown was tasked

00:49:48.860 --> 00:49:51.405
with the same thing with Foo Fighters.

00:49:51.405 --> 00:49:52.531
I mean, there's some other stuff, too,

00:49:52.531 --> 00:49:54.157
that I can't talk about

00:49:54.157 --> 00:49:55.200
that was way before that.

00:49:55.200 --> 00:49:57.703
So you're like, Oh, shit.

00:49:57.703 --> 00:49:58.996
But what did Brown's work

00:49:58.996 --> 00:50:01.415
in Antigravity have to do with UFOs?

00:50:01.415 --> 00:50:03.542
Well, his gravitator looked exactly

00:50:03.542 --> 00:50:04.960
like a flying saucer.

00:50:04.960 --> 00:50:05.877
He found that

00:50:05.877 --> 00:50:07.796
circular craft were better

00:50:07.796 --> 00:50:10.465
for that application than winged craft.

00:50:10.465 --> 00:50:12.092
And behind closed doors,

00:50:12.092 --> 00:50:14.970
Townsend Brown was obsessed with UFOs.

00:50:14.970 --> 00:50:16.722
He even created NICAP,

00:50:16.722 --> 00:50:18.223
the National Investigations

00:50:18.223 --> 00:50:20.225
Committee on Aerial Phenomena.

00:50:20.225 --> 00:50:22.185
When Townsend's daughter, Linda Brown,

00:50:22.185 --> 00:50:23.812
and his biographer requested

00:50:23.812 --> 00:50:25.647
the scientist’s records from the Navy,

00:50:25.647 --> 00:50:27.941
they were at first very uncooperative.

00:50:27.941 --> 00:50:29.651
And then eventually they hinted that

00:50:29.651 --> 00:50:30.402
a lot of Brown's

00:50:30.402 --> 00:50:31.987
work was still classified.

00:50:31.987 --> 00:50:33.155
But why would Brown's work

00:50:33.155 --> 00:50:34.031
be classified

00:50:34.031 --> 00:50:36.074
if he was just a failed hack?

00:50:36.074 --> 00:50:37.492
The National Secrecy Act

00:50:37.492 --> 00:50:38.827
prevented scientists like T.

00:50:38.827 --> 00:50:40.662
Townsend Brown from commercializing

00:50:40.662 --> 00:50:43.415
or even publicizing any technology

00:50:43.415 --> 00:50:45.500
which could potentially be interpreted

00:50:45.500 --> 00:50:47.377
as having a military application.

00:50:47.377 --> 00:50:49.421
Well we know from Schatzkin’s biography

00:50:49.421 --> 00:50:51.423
that Brown actually had meetings

00:50:51.423 --> 00:50:53.383
with the highest level officials

00:50:53.383 --> 00:50:55.260
in American atomic programs,

00:50:55.260 --> 00:50:56.178
people like Edward

00:50:56.178 --> 00:50:57.763
Teller, the father of the hydrogen

00:50:57.763 --> 00:50:58.722
bomb, and General

00:50:58.722 --> 00:50:59.681
Curtis LeMay,

00:50:59.681 --> 00:51:01.266
both deep insiders

00:51:01.266 --> 00:51:02.893
when it came to atomic secrets.

00:51:02.893 --> 00:51:04.478
Townsend Brown's daughter Linda

00:51:04.478 --> 00:51:05.437
even recalls

00:51:05.437 --> 00:51:07.064
that he was often taken home

00:51:07.064 --> 00:51:08.774
in a black Cadillac driven

00:51:08.774 --> 00:51:09.316
by a man

00:51:09.316 --> 00:51:10.692
that she would eventually come

00:51:10.692 --> 00:51:12.652
to know as Robert Sarbacher.

00:51:12.652 --> 00:51:13.862
And where have we heard

00:51:13.862 --> 00:51:15.322
that mysterious name before?

00:51:15.322 --> 00:51:16.239
Sarbacher,

00:51:16.239 --> 00:51:17.949
somebody purportedly involved

00:51:17.949 --> 00:51:19.284
in the stand up of the stuff

00:51:19.284 --> 00:51:20.827
that I uncovered. Right.

00:51:20.827 --> 00:51:22.120
But if you look deeper, things

00:51:22.120 --> 00:51:23.955
get even weirder with Brown.

00:51:23.955 --> 00:51:25.957
In the naval records that we do have,

00:51:25.957 --> 00:51:26.416
it shows

00:51:26.416 --> 00:51:28.335
that Brown was suddenly terminated

00:51:28.335 --> 00:51:30.378
by the Navy in 1942

00:51:30.378 --> 00:51:31.713
with no explanation,

00:51:31.713 --> 00:51:33.673
despite strong performance.

00:51:33.673 --> 00:51:34.466
Two weeks later,

00:51:34.466 --> 00:51:36.968
he mysteriously pops up as an employee

00:51:36.968 --> 00:51:39.096
at Martin Corporation in Burbank,

00:51:39.096 --> 00:51:40.305
just 50 miles

00:51:40.305 --> 00:51:41.348
from where Skunkworks

00:51:41.348 --> 00:51:41.890
is founded

00:51:41.890 --> 00:51:43.558
a year later, by legendary

00:51:43.558 --> 00:51:45.769
aeronautical engineer Kelly Johnson.

00:51:45.769 --> 00:51:47.521
Skunkworks was created to house

00:51:47.521 --> 00:51:50.107
Martin's most advanced, secretive work.

00:51:50.107 --> 00:51:52.025
Over 80% of its current

00:51:52.025 --> 00:51:53.944
projects are still classified.

00:51:53.944 --> 00:51:54.986
Is it a coincidence

00:51:54.986 --> 00:51:55.904
