01:09:00.886 --> 01:09:02.680
You can track the flow of information

01:09:02.680 --> 01:09:04.598
by the uniquely false details in it.

01:09:04.598 --> 01:09:06.767
And you can easily discredit the leak.

01:09:06.767 --> 01:09:08.144
Bob Lazar would hang around

01:09:08.144 --> 01:09:09.728
some interesting characters.

01:09:09.728 --> 01:09:11.230
Guys like John Lear,

01:09:11.230 --> 01:09:12.398
who flew cargo planes

01:09:12.398 --> 01:09:13.983
for the CIA in the seventies.

01:09:13.983 --> 01:09:15.192
Lear definitely seemed

01:09:15.192 --> 01:09:16.569
to spread disinformation

01:09:16.569 --> 01:09:17.736
in other cases.

01:09:17.736 --> 01:09:19.321
He was also the son of Bill

01:09:19.321 --> 01:09:20.281
Lear, inventor

01:09:20.281 --> 01:09:21.115
of the Learjet

01:09:21.115 --> 01:09:22.366
who may have been involved

01:09:22.366 --> 01:09:24.160
in the original UFO program.

01:09:24.160 --> 01:09:26.203
My question is, did John Lear

01:09:26.203 --> 01:09:27.371
manipulate Lazar

01:09:27.371 --> 01:09:28.414
into spreading a bunch

01:09:28.414 --> 01:09:30.416
of pure disinformation?

01:09:30.416 --> 01:09:31.292
And so Lazar's

01:09:31.292 --> 01:09:32.209
claim that he worked on

01:09:32.209 --> 01:09:34.712
UFOs was all a complete lie?

01:09:34.712 --> 01:09:37.131
Or was Lazar just a disclosure test

01:09:37.131 --> 01:09:38.632
for Lear and others around him?

01:09:38.632 --> 01:09:39.884
Let's see how the public

01:09:39.884 --> 01:09:41.135
reacts to this guy.

01:09:41.135 --> 01:09:42.595
He's easy to discredit,

01:09:42.595 --> 01:09:44.054
but mostly telling the truth.

01:09:44.054 --> 01:09:46.223
Personally, I'm not sure what to think

01:09:46.223 --> 01:09:47.975
and would love to meet Lazar myself

01:09:47.975 --> 01:09:49.226
and ask him what he meant

01:09:49.226 --> 01:09:50.686
when he told Jacques Vallee

01:09:50.686 --> 01:09:53.022
about the liquid he was made to drink

01:09:53.022 --> 01:09:54.190
and the memory lapses

01:09:54.190 --> 01:09:55.065
it caused

01:09:55.065 --> 01:09:56.358
and about his relationship

01:09:56.358 --> 01:09:57.484
with John Lear.

01:09:59.111 --> 01:09:59.653
There’s

01:09:59.653 --> 01:10:01.447
probably a small contingency out there

01:10:01.447 --> 01:10:03.115
that says the US needs to

01:10:03.115 --> 01:10:04.450
maintain primacy.

01:10:04.450 --> 01:10:06.368
You have this exotic tech

01:10:06.368 --> 01:10:07.661
that we've found, you know,

01:10:07.661 --> 01:10:09.371
in the case of whatever crashes

01:10:09.371 --> 01:10:10.372
that have occurred.

01:10:10.372 --> 01:10:11.540
We don't know

01:10:11.540 --> 01:10:12.666
exactly what to do with it.

01:10:12.666 --> 01:10:14.168
Maybe we made more progress early

01:10:14.168 --> 01:10:15.586
on than we have now.

01:10:15.586 --> 01:10:16.879
We need to kind of refresh

01:10:16.879 --> 01:10:18.088
the talent pool

01:10:18.088 --> 01:10:19.590
and maybe out ourselves

01:10:19.590 --> 01:10:22.468
as a program and frontrun immunity

01:10:22.468 --> 01:10:24.094
through legislature to do that.

01:10:24.094 --> 01:10:25.179
What do you say to those people

01:10:25.179 --> 01:10:25.930
that- Yeah,

01:10:25.930 --> 01:10:26.680
because I mean, that's something

01:10:26.680 --> 01:10:28.390
I tried to espouse on News Nation.

01:10:28.390 --> 01:10:29.350
I can't remember how they

01:10:29.350 --> 01:10:31.227
edited it or whatever, but

01:10:31.769 --> 01:10:32.561
it actually

01:10:32.561 --> 01:10:34.730
hurts national supremacy

01:10:34.730 --> 01:10:36.607
to keep it obtusely secret.

01:10:36.607 --> 01:10:37.608
Yeah, that's what I’m saying.

01:10:37.608 --> 01:10:38.484
You can't even bring

01:10:38.484 --> 01:10:39.735
the right people on it

01:10:39.735 --> 01:10:43.906
you know
say the best theoretician in quantum

01:10:43.906 --> 01:10:47.284
thermodynamics just happens to

01:10:47.326 --> 01:10:48.702
smoke marijuana

01:10:48.702 --> 01:10:49.954
so he can't get a clearance

01:10:49.954 --> 01:10:51.997
and he can’t get on the program.

01:10:51.997 --> 01:10:54.041
So it actually hurts,

01:10:54.041 --> 01:10:55.417
you know, national security

01:10:55.417 --> 01:10:56.543
by not opening it up,

01:10:56.543 --> 01:10:59.505
at least in an appropriate way,

01:10:59.505 --> 01:11:01.090
that we're not compromising anything

01:11:01.090 --> 01:11:01.840
that somebody could use

01:11:01.840 --> 01:11:04.301
illicitly to hurt people.

01:11:04.301 --> 01:11:05.803
But at least and that's why

01:11:05.803 --> 01:11:07.513
I used the nuclear physics example.

01:11:07.513 --> 01:11:09.515
The program should want to out itself.

01:11:09.515 --> 01:11:09.890
Yeah.

01:11:09.890 --> 01:11:11.809
It's like, yeah, protect

01:11:11.809 --> 01:11:13.185
what could be weaponized. Yeah.

01:11:13.185 --> 01:11:14.228
But generally allow it

01:11:14.228 --> 01:11:16.689
to be studied openly.

01:11:16.689 --> 01:11:17.439
But there's absolutely

01:11:17.439 --> 01:11:18.857
like no cogent plan that

01:11:18.857 --> 01:11:22.069
I'm aware of to do so.

01:11:22.152 --> 01:11:22.820
Congressman, do you

01:11:22.820 --> 01:11:24.738
think that these reverse engineering

01:11:24.738 --> 01:11:26.407
programs have made any progress

01:11:26.407 --> 01:11:27.449
or do you think. Yeah, I do.

01:11:27.449 --> 01:11:28.242
I just don't think they

01:11:28.242 --> 01:11:29.326
they're going to scratch-

01:11:29.326 --> 01:11:31.370
because if they did

01:11:31.370 --> 01:11:32.830
we wouldn't- we would own the skies

01:11:32.830 --> 01:11:33.956
if they had it.

01:11:33.956 --> 01:11:34.415
Isn't it

01:11:34.415 --> 01:11:35.416
in their best interest

01:11:35.416 --> 01:11:36.750
to just get immunity for themselves

01:11:36.750 --> 01:11:38.294
and try to refresh the talent pool

01:11:38.294 --> 01:11:40.004
if these people are you know, it's

01:11:40.004 --> 01:11:41.213
they're all old and it's

01:11:41.213 --> 01:11:42.631
completely compartmentalized

01:11:42.631 --> 01:11:43.716
and they haven't made you know,

01:11:43.716 --> 01:11:44.425
and the Wilson memo.

01:11:44.425 --> 01:11:46.218
They’re completely arrogant.

01:11:46.218 --> 01:11:47.386
They're arrogant. Blatantly arrogant.

01:11:47.386 --> 01:11:48.345
They're above the laws

01:11:48.345 --> 01:11:48.971
and they're above-

01:11:48.971 --> 01:11:49.930
why aren’t

01:11:49.930 --> 01:11:51.181
they releasing the Kennedy files?

01:11:51.181 --> 01:11:52.975
Nobodies allowed in sixty years,

01:11:52.975 --> 01:11:53.684
but every president-

01:11:53.684 --> 01:11:54.852
you think there’s a connection

01:11:54.852 --> 01:11:56.437
between that and this?

01:11:56.437 --> 01:11:57.021
I heard,

01:11:57.021 --> 01:11:57.396
I've heard

01:11:57.396 --> 01:11:58.480
that I would hate to speculate.

01:11:58.480 --> 01:12:02.026
I’m more just- I want it to surface.

01:12:02.026 --> 01:12:03.027
Just give me the start.

01:12:03.027 --> 01:12:04.403
Gotcha. Thank you.

01:12:06.030 --> 01:12:06.822
We must guard

01:12:06.822 --> 01:12:08.532
against the acquisition

01:12:08.532 --> 01:12:10.242
of unwarranted influence,

01:12:10.242 --> 01:12:12.202
whether sought or unsought,

01:12:12.202 --> 01:12:14.955
by the military industrial complex.

01:12:14.955 --> 01:12:16.206
I have no idea

01:12:16.206 --> 01:12:17.166
if JFK’s death

01:12:17.166 --> 01:12:19.043
had anything to do with UFOs.

01:12:19.043 --> 01:12:20.461
But there is a letter

01:12:20.461 --> 01:12:22.504
that was supposedly declassified due

01:12:22.504 --> 01:12:23.881
to a Freedom of Information

01:12:23.881 --> 01:12:25.966
Act request in 2006.

01:12:25.966 --> 01:12:27.176
It was from JFK

01:12:27.176 --> 01:12:28.844
to the director of the CIA

01:12:28.844 --> 01:12:31.388
at the time, John McCone. Its date?

01:12:31.388 --> 01:12:34.808
November 12th, 1963, just ten days

01:12:34.808 --> 01:12:36.643
before the president's assassination.

01:12:36.643 --> 01:12:38.020
In the letter, JFK

01:12:38.020 --> 01:12:39.646
is asking for the full data

01:12:39.646 --> 01:12:41.982
on unknowns or UFOs

01:12:41.982 --> 01:12:43.609
so we can coordinate more tightly

01:12:43.609 --> 01:12:45.611
with Russians in space.

01:12:45.611 --> 01:12:46.570
And they don't mistake

01:12:46.570 --> 01:12:48.113
these UFOs as acts

01:12:48.113 --> 01:12:49.198
of American aggression

01:12:49.198 --> 01:12:50.324
or reconnaissance.

01:12:50.324 --> 01:12:51.492
I've called the guy

01:12:51.492 --> 01:12:53.077
who used the Freedom of Information

01:12:53.077 --> 01:12:54.620
Act to retrieve this document

01:12:54.620 --> 01:12:56.038
like five times now,

01:12:56.038 --> 01:12:57.331
and he's not playing ball.

01:12:57.331 --> 01:12:58.457
So I have no idea

01:12:58.457 --> 01:12:59.833
if this document is real.

01:12:59.833 --> 01:13:01.543
And an anonymous archivist

01:13:01.543 --> 01:13:02.169
that handles

01:13:02.169 --> 01:13:03.587
a lot of JFK's letters

01:13:03.587 --> 01:13:05.172
say that there are some anomalies

01:13:05.172 --> 01:13:07.007
in the letter that make him skeptical.

01:13:07.007 --> 01:13:07.966
So who knows?

01:13:07.966 --> 01:13:08.801
But I will say

01:13:08.801 --> 01:13:10.803
this is a very weird non-sequitur

01:13:10.803 --> 01:13:12.346
from former CIA Director

01:13:12.346 --> 01:13:14.056
Mike Pompeo, when asked why

01:13:14.056 --> 01:13:15.265
the nearly 5000

01:13:15.265 --> 01:13:16.141
JFK files

01:13:16.141 --> 01:13:18.727
still won't be released to this day.

01:13:18.727 --> 01:13:19.978
Why did you fight to keep

01:13:19.978 --> 01:13:21.855
the JFK files secret?

01:13:21.855 --> 01:13:23.148
These don't hold the dark secrets

01:13:23.148 --> 01:13:23.899
that everybody wants

01:13:23.899 --> 01:13:25.484
to just hold up as the boogeyman.

01:13:25.484 --> 01:13:27.361
I saw the UFO files, too.

01:13:27.361 --> 01:13:28.904
We've got bigger problems.

01:13:31.323 --> 01:13:32.741
What do you say to the people who say

01:13:32.741 --> 01:13:34.076
this is a psyop

01:13:34.076 --> 01:13:35.077
and they just want

01:13:35.077 --> 01:13:36.620
black budget funding?

01:13:36.620 --> 01:13:37.871
So the information might be right,

01:13:37.871 --> 01:13:39.331
but they just want to be able

01:13:39.331 --> 01:13:41.250
to have increased surveillance

01:13:41.250 --> 01:13:43.335
in the skies and in space or whatever.

01:13:43.335 --> 01:13:43.669
Yeah,

01:13:43.669 --> 01:13:44.378
that comes up

01:13:44.378 --> 01:13:45.295
I think with some people

01:13:45.295 --> 01:13:46.547
that have like an issue with it

01:13:46.547 --> 01:13:48.048
where you had to remember

01:13:48.048 --> 01:13:49.299
like national security threat

01:13:49.299 --> 01:13:50.801
is the way to get Congress

01:13:50.801 --> 01:13:52.177
alerted and engaged.

01:13:52.177 --> 01:13:55.139
That is like the operative word

01:13:55.139 --> 01:13:57.057
that Congress responds to.

01:13:57.057 --> 01:13:58.267
The narrative

01:13:58.267 --> 01:13:59.476
that this could be a threat.

01:13:59.476 --> 01:14:00.978
Because, look, to be honest with you,

01:14:00.978 --> 01:14:02.229
I think this stuff's been going on

01:14:02.229 --> 01:14:03.522
for thousands of years.

01:14:03.522 --> 01:14:05.482
And so it does frustrate me

01:14:05.482 --> 01:14:07.109
a little bit when it's like,

01:14:07.109 --> 01:14:09.278
you know,
we need to be able to

01:14:09.278 --> 01:14:10.362
shoot these things down.

01:14:10.362 --> 01:14:12.489
It's like,
I don't think they’re really a,

01:14:12.489 --> 01:14:12.823
you know,

01:14:12.823 --> 01:14:14.491
an immediate existential threat

01:14:14.491 --> 01:14:15.909
as my- as my strong bias.

01:14:15.909 --> 01:14:16.410
It might not be

01:14:16.410 --> 01:14:19.121
the smartest idea to try to fire back

01:14:19.121 --> 01:14:20.414
when they're not firing at you.

01:14:20.414 --> 01:14:21.290
They'll take you out

01:14:21.290 --> 01:14:21.999
real quick

01:14:21.999 --> 01:14:23.500
if they can fly faster than light

01:14:23.500 --> 01:14:25.210
and do all the stuff they're doing.

01:14:25.210 --> 01:14:27.296
So yeah, it's probably not a good idea.

01:14:27.296 --> 01:14:28.630
We probably shouldn't

01:14:28.630 --> 01:14:30.966
attack the zookeeper.

01:14:30.966 --> 01:14:32.050
Yeah, exactly.

01:14:32.050 --> 01:14:33.051
Don’t attack the zookeeper.

01:14:33.051 --> 01:14:34.803
Like, that's probably not a good idea.

01:14:34.803 --> 01:14:36.346
Stick to the facts,

01:14:36.346 --> 01:14:37.389
write it down and don't

01:14:37.389 --> 01:14:38.765
speculate what you think it is

01:14:38.765 --> 01:14:39.975
because it will sway your decision.

01:14:39.975 --> 01:14:41.351
The thing that frustrated me

01:14:41.351 --> 01:14:43.395
about the hearing was,

01:14:43.395 --> 01:14:45.772
look, I think Ryan Graves is awesome.

01:14:45.772 --> 01:14:47.024
And I think as is commander,

01:14:47.024 --> 01:14:47.483
David Fravor.

01:14:47.483 --> 01:14:48.066
I think they're showing

01:14:48.066 --> 01:14:49.026
a lot of courage.

01:14:49.026 --> 01:14:51.278
But it felt like their simple take away

01:14:51.278 --> 01:14:52.988
is we need more sensors

01:14:52.988 --> 01:14:54.698
and we need a better collection process

01:14:54.698 --> 01:14:55.991
and a more standard taxonomy,

01:14:55.991 --> 01:14:58.368
all of which are very important.

01:14:58.368 --> 01:15:00.662
But it's this kind of lazy data story

01:15:00.662 --> 01:15:02.915
that I think comes from Silicon Valley,

01:15:02.915 --> 01:15:03.665
where it's like

01:15:03.665 --> 01:15:04.291
if we just get

01:15:04.291 --> 01:15:06.793
a bigger database of the UFOs,

01:15:06.793 --> 01:15:07.336
a machine

01:15:07.336 --> 01:15:08.420
learning classifier

01:15:08.420 --> 01:15:10.547
will somehow spit out the answer

01:15:10.547 --> 01:15:11.590
as to what they are.

01:15:11.590 --> 01:15:11.965
Yeah,

01:15:11.965 --> 01:15:12.549
the only thing you're going

01:15:12.549 --> 01:15:13.967
to get from external observation,

01:15:13.967 --> 01:15:14.968
at least through the lens

01:15:14.968 --> 01:15:15.886
I look through, right.

01:15:15.886 --> 01:15:16.637
You're going to get what they call

01:15:16.637 --> 01:15:18.805
activity based intelligence, ABI.

01:15:18.805 --> 01:15:19.515
You'll figure out where

01:15:19.515 --> 01:15:20.849
the true hotspots are,

01:15:20.849 --> 01:15:22.768
but it's not the end all, be all.

01:15:22.768 --> 01:15:24.353
If you have- you're trying

01:15:24.353 --> 01:15:25.771
to find a needle in a haystack,

01:15:25.771 --> 01:15:28.398
you don't want to add to the haystack.

01:15:28.398 --> 01:15:30.692
And I think we are overindexed

01:15:30.692 --> 01:15:32.528
on- Yeah, saturated with data.

01:15:32.528 --> 01:15:34.613
Oversaturated with data in some ways,

01:15:34.613 --> 01:15:35.656
and it could be probably

01:15:35.656 --> 01:15:36.615
better standardized.

01:15:36.615 --> 01:15:38.242
So I'll give them that.

01:15:38.242 --> 01:15:40.118
But we're under indexed on theory,

01:15:40.118 --> 01:15:41.036
and to my mind,

01:15:41.036 --> 01:15:42.538
we have one

01:15:42.538 --> 01:15:44.414
pretty strong theoretician

01:15:44.414 --> 01:15:46.542
and Jacques Vallee.

01:15:46.542 --> 01:15:48.043
Who really, if you read

01:15:48.043 --> 01:15:49.336
like The Invisible College,

01:15:49.336 --> 01:15:51.129
which he wrote in 1975,

01:15:51.129 --> 01:15:54.007
that is the tip of the spear now,

01:15:54.007 --> 01:15:55.884
in terms of theory on UFOs,

01:15:55.884 --> 01:15:57.844
which is wild to me.

01:15:57.844 --> 01:15:58.720
Jacques Vallee

01:15:58.720 --> 01:16:00.264
might be the most preeminent

01:16:00.264 --> 01:16:02.391
UFO researcher in the world.

01:16:02.391 --> 01:16:03.058
In fact,

01:16:03.058 --> 01:16:05.143
he was Steven Spielberg's inspiration

01:16:05.143 --> 01:16:06.436
for the eccentric French

01:16:06.436 --> 01:16:08.855
scientist played by Francois Truffaut

01:16:08.855 --> 01:16:10.899
in Close Encounters of the Third Kind.

01:16:10.899 --> 01:16:13.569
Yeah,
nobody's really replaced him

01:16:13.569 --> 01:16:15.070
at that level.

01:16:15.070 --> 01:16:17.322
And especially hypotheses

01:16:17.322 --> 01:16:19.157
that are even a little more testable.

01:16:19.157 --> 01:16:20.534
But what the average person

01:16:20.534 --> 01:16:22.327
might not know about Jacques

01:16:22.327 --> 01:16:24.830
is that he's obsessed with time travel.

01:16:24.830 --> 01:16:25.539
In fact,

01:16:25.539 --> 01:16:26.873
on the set of Close Encounters,

01:16:26.873 --> 01:16:28.041
he got into an argument

01:16:28.041 --> 01:16:29.167
with Steven Spielberg.

01:16:29.167 --> 01:16:30.544
And we had a long discussion

01:16:30.544 --> 01:16:32.087
about what UFOs could be.

01:16:32.087 --> 01:16:33.880
And of course, for him,

01:16:33.880 --> 01:16:36.300
the main point of of

01:16:36.300 --> 01:16:37.884
the movie was entertainment,

01:16:37.884 --> 01:16:40.345
and it was appropriate for the UFOs

01:16:40.345 --> 01:16:42.931
to be extraterrestrial visitors.

01:16:42.931 --> 01:16:44.391
Jacques wanted the UFOs

01:16:44.391 --> 01:16:45.684
and the aliens in the movie

01:16:45.684 --> 01:16:48.186
to be represented in a more nuanced way

01:16:48.186 --> 01:16:50.105
and actually linked with time travel,

01:16:50.105 --> 01:16:51.440
not just space travel.

01:16:51.440 --> 01:16:52.649
I think that

01:16:52.649 --> 01:16:54.735
the extraterrestrial hypothesis

01:16:54.735 --> 01:16:57.070
is actually more farfetched.

01:16:57.070 --> 01:16:57.904
I think the idea

01:16:57.904 --> 01:16:59.656
that another species

01:16:59.656 --> 01:17:01.783
would evolutionarily converge

01:17:01.783 --> 01:17:03.243
to be bipedal,

01:17:03.243 --> 01:17:05.370
to have kind of the symmetric,

01:17:05.370 --> 01:17:07.956
you know, bipedal- bilateral symmetry.

01:17:07.956 --> 01:17:09.374
Yeah.
Because if we look at like

01:17:09.374 --> 01:17:11.043
the Aeriel School event,

01:17:11.043 --> 01:17:12.961
you know,
if we believe the 100 schoolchildren

01:17:12.961 --> 01:17:15.047
that saw bipedal,

01:17:15.047 --> 01:17:18.425
you know, hominid looking kind of NHI.

01:17:18.425 --> 01:17:20.135
That seems

01:17:20.135 --> 01:17:21.011
pretty rare to

01:17:21.011 --> 01:17:22.262
have the same development

