01:25:50.687 --> 01:25:52.313
have this sort of Goldilocks

01:25:52.313 --> 01:25:53.773
perfect habitable zone.

01:25:53.773 --> 01:25:54.566
Oh, yeah.

01:25:54.566 --> 01:25:55.900
I mean, Earth's like very finely

01:25:55.900 --> 01:25:56.484
tuned, right?

01:25:56.484 --> 01:25:56.985
The temperature

01:25:56.985 --> 01:25:58.778
gradient is just enough.

01:25:58.778 --> 01:26:00.697
Is that a coincidence or did

01:26:00.697 --> 01:26:02.157
aliens set this up? I don't know.

01:26:02.157 --> 01:26:02.991
You can even think

01:26:02.991 --> 01:26:04.159
of, like, Heisenberg’s

01:26:04.159 --> 01:26:05.368
uncertainty principle

01:26:05.368 --> 01:26:06.202
where you can't measure

01:26:06.202 --> 01:26:07.996
position and momentum at the same time

01:26:07.996 --> 01:26:08.329
as like

01:26:08.329 --> 01:26:10.748
a computational caching function.

01:26:10.748 --> 01:26:11.541
Oh, interesting.

01:26:11.541 --> 01:26:13.459
You can’t compute everything- Yeah.

01:26:13.459 --> 01:26:15.211
Your RAM’s not that good.

01:26:21.009 --> 01:26:23.178
And maybe if we are in a simulation,

01:26:23.178 --> 01:26:24.804
our perceptive capabilities

01:26:24.804 --> 01:26:26.347
were artificially limited

01:26:26.347 --> 01:26:27.515
by the simulators.

01:26:27.515 --> 01:26:29.851
We only see between 400 and 700

01:26:29.851 --> 01:26:30.727
hundred nanometers

01:26:30.727 --> 01:26:32.729
of the electromagnetic wave spectrum.

01:26:32.729 --> 01:26:34.772
We only hear certain frequencies.

01:26:34.772 --> 01:26:35.607
That's why dog

01:26:35.607 --> 01:26:37.442
whistles are inaudible to humans.

01:26:37.442 --> 01:26:39.402
If we really wanted to create safe,

01:26:39.402 --> 01:26:41.196
artificial general intelligence,

01:26:41.196 --> 01:26:42.989
we might initially experiment

01:26:42.989 --> 01:26:44.157
with artificial life

01:26:44.157 --> 01:26:46.201
so limited in its perception

01:26:46.201 --> 01:26:48.578
that it doesn't even know we exist.

01:26:48.578 --> 01:26:50.079
So it definitely can't hurt us.

01:26:50.079 --> 01:26:50.622
Forward

01:26:50.622 --> 01:26:52.415
looking infrared caught the famous

01:26:52.415 --> 01:26:54.500
tic tac video in 2004.

01:26:54.500 --> 01:26:56.294
What if we had infrared sensors,

01:26:56.294 --> 01:26:57.754
or for that matter, gravity

01:26:57.754 --> 01:26:59.631
wave detectors in our pockets?

01:26:59.631 --> 01:27:01.549
How many more sightings would we have?

01:27:01.549 --> 01:27:02.425
That explains

01:27:02.425 --> 01:27:04.385
why UFOs are disproportionately

01:27:04.385 --> 01:27:06.512
picked up by military bases.

01:27:06.512 --> 01:27:09.015
It's the robust multi-sensory detection

01:27:09.015 --> 01:27:10.391
that you find on those bases

01:27:10.391 --> 01:27:11.851
that makes all the difference.

01:27:13.394 --> 01:27:13.811
There is

01:27:13.811 --> 01:27:17.690
no understanding of alien visits

01:27:17.774 --> 01:27:20.443
that has them only visit restricted

01:27:20.443 --> 01:27:21.819
Navy airspace

01:27:21.819 --> 01:27:23.696
to be picked up by pilots.

01:27:23.988 --> 01:27:25.448
It’s an observer and collection

01:27:25.448 --> 01:27:26.324
bias issue,

01:27:26.324 --> 01:27:28.284
where you have all the eyeballs

01:27:28.284 --> 01:27:29.744
and all the sensors in those areas.

01:27:29.744 --> 01:27:30.620
Sure, that's a good point.

01:27:30.620 --> 01:27:32.372
You know,
if you were to do an activity

01:27:32.372 --> 01:27:33.581
based intelligence

01:27:33.581 --> 01:27:34.499
across the globe,

01:27:34.499 --> 01:27:36.584
if we actually can have an open

01:27:36.584 --> 01:27:38.253
and honest kind of collection system.

01:27:38.253 --> 01:27:39.254
Yeah.

01:27:39.254 --> 01:27:40.255
I think we'd probably see

01:27:40.255 --> 01:27:41.047
some hot spots

01:27:41.047 --> 01:27:41.923
that don't even make any sense.

01:27:41.923 --> 01:27:43.258
You know I don’t like throwing shade,

01:27:43.258 --> 01:27:44.759
but like Neil deGrasse Tyson, right?

01:27:44.759 --> 01:27:46.719
Oh, yeah, He's made up his mind.

01:27:46.719 --> 01:27:48.888
I've read his tweets and I'm like,

01:27:48.888 --> 01:27:50.348
Dude, you have a Ph.D. in physics?

01:27:50.348 --> 01:27:51.641
Where's your curiosity?

01:27:51.641 --> 01:27:52.934
I can't even believe.

01:27:52.934 --> 01:27:54.310
There's no evidence

01:27:54.310 --> 01:27:55.395
that would convince

01:27:55.395 --> 01:27:56.854
an authentic skeptic.

01:27:56.854 --> 01:27:58.189
I have credentials too

01:27:58.189 --> 01:27:59.274
and I'm happy to go

01:27:59.274 --> 01:28:00.525
toe to toe with you.

01:28:00.525 --> 01:28:02.235
Yeah. If he wants to debate me, I'd be.

01:28:02.235 --> 01:28:03.486
I'd be fine with that.

01:28:07.448 --> 01:28:08.116
You know, when I started

01:28:08.116 --> 01:28:09.117
studying physics in college,

01:28:09.117 --> 01:28:11.035
and I became an intel guy,

01:28:11.035 --> 01:28:13.621
and I got briefed a lot of programs.

01:28:13.621 --> 01:28:14.205
I figured, oh,

01:28:14.205 --> 01:28:16.874
I would know if it's a thing.

01:28:16.874 --> 01:28:18.668
And I kind of ascribe to the,

01:28:18.668 --> 01:28:21.337
you know, the Enrico Fermi thing where,

01:28:21.337 --> 01:28:22.130
you know,

01:28:22.130 --> 01:28:23.256
wouldn't it be obvious, wouldn’t

01:28:23.256 --> 01:28:24.841
they just be flying

01:28:24.841 --> 01:28:26.926
and and they wouldn't care

01:28:26.926 --> 01:28:28.928
and they would just land and say hello?

01:28:28.928 --> 01:28:31.931
But that's like an overly simplistic

01:28:31.931 --> 01:28:33.766
thought, you know- humanistic too.

01:28:33.766 --> 01:28:34.934
Very humanistic.

01:28:34.934 --> 01:28:36.102
You're
assuming that they have

01:28:36.102 --> 01:28:38.187
the same kind of intent as us.

01:28:38.187 --> 01:28:40.690
You, you assume they operate

01:28:40.690 --> 01:28:42.400
in the electromagnetic spectrum

01:28:42.400 --> 01:28:44.485
that we can observe normally.

01:28:44.485 --> 01:28:46.237
And then also

01:28:46.237 --> 01:28:47.739
you're assuming that they would want

01:28:47.739 --> 01:28:50.116
this kind of open, obvious

01:28:50.116 --> 01:28:51.367
kind of interaction

01:28:51.367 --> 01:28:52.994
and they're not doing cover

01:28:52.994 --> 01:28:54.203
concealment techniques.

01:28:54.203 --> 01:28:54.912
Where they're,

01:28:54.912 --> 01:28:56.414
you know,
obfuscating their activity

01:28:56.414 --> 01:28:58.499
because maybe they're, you know,

01:28:58.583 --> 01:29:00.460
observing us for some purpose.

01:29:00.460 --> 01:29:01.753
Or what if they're von Neumann

01:29:01.753 --> 01:29:02.587
probes, right.

01:29:02.587 --> 01:29:04.005
Do you guys know von Neumann probes?

01:29:04.005 --> 01:29:06.299
No. Von Neumann replicators.

01:29:06.299 --> 01:29:08.551
Well, just like self-replicating tech

01:29:09.594 --> 01:29:11.804
that if that's disposable in nature,

01:29:11.804 --> 01:29:13.056
if you're trying to send something out

01:29:13.056 --> 01:29:14.223
simple and engineered

01:29:14.223 --> 01:29:16.142
to explore the cosmos.

01:29:16.142 --> 01:29:17.977
And there's always a question of like

01:29:17.977 --> 01:29:18.978
what was the first

01:29:18.978 --> 01:29:20.855
self-replicating organism?

01:29:20.855 --> 01:29:22.774
I think the big mystery is

01:29:22.774 --> 01:29:25.485
how does chemistry turn into biology?

01:29:25.485 --> 01:29:26.569
And we have this

01:29:26.569 --> 01:29:27.612
these people that say, Oh,

01:29:27.612 --> 01:29:28.029
it was just

01:29:28.029 --> 01:29:29.655
this primordial soup,

01:29:29.655 --> 01:29:30.740
and you had all these chemicals

01:29:30.740 --> 01:29:32.075
kind of like floating around

01:29:32.075 --> 01:29:33.576
and they've done experiments like this

01:29:33.576 --> 01:29:35.244
and never been able to recreate life

01:29:35.244 --> 01:29:36.746
through those experiments.

01:29:36.746 --> 01:29:38.790
And it's a really open question,

01:29:38.790 --> 01:29:41.376
like how did life form?

01:29:41.376 --> 01:29:41.918
And I think it's

01:29:41.918 --> 01:29:43.086
probably much more trippy

01:29:43.086 --> 01:29:44.796
and interesting than like

01:29:44.796 --> 01:29:45.755
just a chemical soup,

01:29:45.755 --> 01:29:46.672
just the chemicals happen

01:29:46.672 --> 01:29:47.715
to bond in a certain way.

01:29:47.715 --> 01:29:48.883
It's a happy accident.

01:29:48.883 --> 01:29:50.259
And Crick's view was

01:29:50.259 --> 01:29:52.095
that DNA could not have emerged

01:29:52.095 --> 01:29:53.262
accidentally

01:29:53.262 --> 01:29:54.263
from the primeval

01:29:54.263 --> 01:29:55.890
soup on this planet

01:29:55.890 --> 01:29:57.767
in just 100 million years.

01:29:57.767 --> 01:29:59.811
It needed much longer to-

01:29:59.811 --> 01:30:01.771
he still bought into the primeval

01:30:01.771 --> 01:30:03.940
soup idea, but not on this planet. Yes.

01:30:03.940 --> 01:30:05.274
What he came down to was that

01:30:05.274 --> 01:30:06.692
there must have been some other planet

01:30:06.692 --> 01:30:07.777
somewhere else

01:30:07.777 --> 01:30:10.530
where a primeval soup had existed

01:30:10.530 --> 01:30:12.573
and there had been enough time

01:30:12.573 --> 01:30:14.534
for DNA to emerge

01:30:14.534 --> 01:30:15.743
from the accidental bumping

01:30:15.743 --> 01:30:16.536
together of molecules.

01:30:16.536 --> 01:30:16.994
That's, by the way,

01:30:16.994 --> 01:30:17.745
something I'm a bit

01:30:17.745 --> 01:30:19.288
skeptical of anywhere.

01:30:19.288 --> 01:30:21.416
There's actually a French

01:30:21.416 --> 01:30:22.583
kind of evolutionary

01:30:22.583 --> 01:30:24.252
theorist and philosopher named

01:30:24.252 --> 01:30:25.461
Henri Bergson.

01:30:25.461 --> 01:30:26.796
He thought the sun was

01:30:26.796 --> 01:30:29.298
somehow essential to evolution.

01:30:29.298 --> 01:30:30.174
If you think about it,

01:30:30.174 --> 01:30:32.427
that makes sense. Mutations.

01:30:32.427 --> 01:30:33.344
You need mutation.

01:30:33.344 --> 01:30:34.512
You need genetic mutations

01:30:34.512 --> 01:30:35.096
for evolution to occur.

01:30:35.096 --> 01:30:36.639
It’s a radiological

01:30:36.639 --> 01:30:36.973
you know, it's

01:30:36.973 --> 01:30:38.641
at least putting out ultraviolet,

01:30:38.641 --> 01:30:39.767
you know. Totally.

01:30:39.767 --> 01:30:42.311
Why are we worried about a Japanese

01:30:42.311 --> 01:30:43.104
nuclear spill?

01:30:43.104 --> 01:30:44.188
What happened at Fukushima

01:30:44.188 --> 01:30:44.856
and Chernobyl?

01:30:44.856 --> 01:30:46.524
You had an acceleration of

01:30:46.524 --> 01:30:48.276
evolution due to radiation.

01:30:49.694 --> 01:30:50.903
Maybe the sun is an

01:30:50.903 --> 01:30:52.405
extremely sophisticated

01:30:52.405 --> 01:30:53.698
nuclear fusion reactor

01:30:53.698 --> 01:30:55.032
that powers the earth.

01:30:55.032 --> 01:30:56.951
And the Earth's electromagnetic field

01:30:56.951 --> 01:30:59.078
was simulated to support life.

01:30:59.078 --> 01:31:01.330
Astronauts often have to take Schumann

01:31:01.330 --> 01:31:02.665
resonance machines up

01:31:02.665 --> 01:31:04.250
with them to space to mimic

01:31:04.250 --> 01:31:06.252
the electromagnetic field of the earth.

01:31:06.252 --> 01:31:07.587
Otherwise their bodies

01:31:07.587 --> 01:31:08.713
often malfunction.

01:31:08.713 --> 01:31:09.338
You know,
if you put

01:31:09.338 --> 01:31:13.217
a frog embryo in a Faraday cage,

01:31:13.301 --> 01:31:15.178
it does not develop normally.

01:31:15.178 --> 01:31:18.264
And then if you can change

01:31:18.389 --> 01:31:20.766
the cell gradient

01:31:20.766 --> 01:31:23.227
of like a tadpole,

01:31:23.227 --> 01:31:24.520
where you've severed the

01:31:24.520 --> 01:31:26.230
the arm of the tadpole

01:31:26.230 --> 01:31:27.356
to the cell gradients

01:31:27.356 --> 01:31:28.274
of the head cells,

01:31:28.274 --> 01:31:29.025
and you can grow

01:31:29.025 --> 01:31:30.526
a, you know, a chimeric

01:31:30.526 --> 01:31:32.153
two headed tadpole.

01:31:32.153 --> 01:31:33.738
And so there's something around

01:31:33.738 --> 01:31:35.156
kind of the electromagnetic field

01:31:35.156 --> 01:31:37.033
that is orthogonal

01:31:37.033 --> 01:31:39.035
and maybe even upstream of DNA

01:31:39.035 --> 01:31:41.245
in terms of morphology.

01:31:41.245 --> 01:31:41.954
Yeah, because they've done

01:31:41.954 --> 01:31:44.081
an experiment too with

01:31:44.081 --> 01:31:45.374
plant growth around

01:31:45.374 --> 01:31:46.042
high powerful

01:31:46.042 --> 01:31:47.668
wi-fi routers and that actually-

01:31:47.668 --> 01:31:50.296
Oh yeah- They don't grow right.

01:31:50.296 --> 01:31:51.297
It's like pretty- It’s

01:31:51.297 --> 01:31:52.173
actually kind of concerning

01:31:52.173 --> 01:31:53.424
I think about the wi-fi in my house.

01:31:53.424 --> 01:31:54.133
I’m like, Oh man.

01:31:54.133 --> 01:31:55.343
Am I like cooking myself

01:31:55.343 --> 01:31:56.427
slowly or something?

01:32:11.400 --> 01:32:12.401
What's the name of the llama?

01:32:12.401 --> 01:32:13.611
Playboy. Playboy.

01:32:14.529 --> 01:32:16.030
I think the name of the llama was Boy.

01:32:31.629 --> 01:32:32.588
Over the past days,

01:32:32.588 --> 01:32:33.506
you shared with us

01:32:33.506 --> 01:32:36.467
that you were diagnosed

01:32:36.467 --> 01:32:38.803
to be on the autism spectrum.

01:32:38.803 --> 01:32:41.180
How has this served you in your life

01:32:41.180 --> 01:32:42.056
and in your career,

01:32:42.056 --> 01:32:44.016
and how has it hindered you?

01:32:44.016 --> 01:32:47.895
Yeah, I mean, I didn't know, you know,

01:32:47.979 --> 01:32:48.938
that I was autistic

01:32:48.938 --> 01:32:50.648
until I was like in my early thirties.

01:32:50.648 --> 01:32:51.607
So, I mean, it served me

01:32:51.607 --> 01:32:52.567
well in the government

01:32:52.567 --> 01:32:54.318
because I was super good at,

01:32:54.318 --> 01:32:56.320
you know,
doing intel and like, you know.

01:32:56.320 --> 01:32:56.988
Dave,

01:32:56.988 --> 01:32:59.991
we want you to target this facility.

01:32:59.991 --> 01:33:00.825
Okay.

01:33:00.825 --> 01:33:01.784
You have six months,

01:33:01.784 --> 01:33:02.660
figure out everything.

01:33:02.660 --> 01:33:04.453
You know, and of course I do.

01:33:04.453 --> 01:33:05.746
And it's, you know, that was very good.

01:33:05.746 --> 01:33:06.831
But I think

01:33:06.831 --> 01:33:07.915
especially if you're trying

01:33:07.915 --> 01:33:09.667
to maintain relationships and stuff

01:33:09.667 --> 01:33:12.795
and how to read people's emotions and

01:33:12.962 --> 01:33:14.547
and how to show your own emotions

01:33:14.547 --> 01:33:15.715
because, you know, autists,

01:33:15.715 --> 01:33:17.717
especially if you're,

01:33:17.800 --> 01:33:18.509
you know, deeper

01:33:18.509 --> 01:33:21.053
in the spectrum when you get Asperger's

01:33:21.053 --> 01:33:22.388
and that kind of stuff.

01:33:22.388 --> 01:33:25.474
You don't know how to even

01:33:25.600 --> 01:33:26.517
present your emotions

01:33:26.517 --> 01:33:28.185
in a way to a partner or,

01:33:28.185 --> 01:33:29.353
you know, spouse or whatever.

01:33:29.353 --> 01:33:30.021
He would come home

01:33:30.021 --> 01:33:30.730
and tell me

01:33:30.730 --> 01:33:32.773
general stuff and I'd be like,

01:33:32.773 --> 01:33:34.817
Yeah, that makes sense.

01:33:34.817 --> 01:33:36.193
Yeah, there's probably aliens.

01:33:36.193 --> 01:33:39.071
Like that makes sense.

01:33:39.071 --> 01:33:40.239
Unfortunately, Dave

01:33:40.239 --> 01:33:41.949
can't talk about the backlash he's

01:33:41.949 --> 01:33:43.868
received from inside the government

01:33:43.868 --> 01:33:45.995
because of an ongoing investigation,

01:33:45.995 --> 01:33:47.622
but a good example of a pretty

01:33:47.622 --> 01:33:49.206
despicable marginalization

01:33:49.206 --> 01:33:50.958
attempt from the outside

01:33:50.958 --> 01:33:52.710
was an article written a few weeks

01:33:52.710 --> 01:33:54.712
after the hearing by The Intercept.

01:33:54.712 --> 01:33:55.796
The article describes

01:33:55.796 --> 01:33:57.089
Dave's hospitalization

01:33:57.089 --> 01:33:58.424
back in 2018,

01:33:58.424 --> 01:33:59.800
an episode of alcohol

01:33:59.800 --> 01:34:01.927
consumption and suicidal ideation

01:34:01.927 --> 01:34:03.638
that led to a 911 call.

01:34:03.638 --> 01:34:05.181
But the article failed to mention

01:34:05.181 --> 01:34:06.223
any of the factors

01:34:06.223 --> 01:34:07.516
that led to this incident.

01:34:07.516 --> 01:34:08.017
You know,

01:34:08.017 --> 01:34:08.851
definitely experienced

01:34:08.851 --> 01:34:10.603
some really nuts stuff.

01:34:10.603 --> 01:34:11.646
Not only has Dave

01:34:11.646 --> 01:34:13.272
been very open with us

01:34:13.272 --> 01:34:15.608
and other media about his PTSD

01:34:15.608 --> 01:34:17.109
from combat experience

01:34:17.109 --> 01:34:18.736
and having a close friend die

01:34:18.736 --> 01:34:19.612
while on duty.

01:34:19.612 --> 01:34:20.821
I had a friend of mine that died

01:34:20.821 --> 01:34:21.614
doing the same stuff

01:34:21.614 --> 01:34:23.741
I was, you know, six months later

01:34:23.741 --> 01:34:25.284
going to the same locations.

01:34:25.284 --> 01:34:26.369
He's also discussed

01:34:26.369 --> 01:34:27.370
all of the suffering

01:34:27.370 --> 01:34:29.372
that's resulted from that experience

01:34:29.372 --> 01:34:30.998
and the proactive techniques

01:34:30.998 --> 01:34:32.792
he's used to heal from that trauma.

01:34:32.792 --> 01:34:34.794
So like EMDR therapy,

01:34:34.794 --> 01:34:37.880
HRV breath work, all that stuff.

01:34:38.005 --> 01:34:39.507
I was not a believer,

01:34:39.507 --> 01:34:40.216
but holy crap,

01:34:40.216 --> 01:34:41.175
at least it worked for me.

01:34:41.175 --> 01:34:42.218
And I highly recommend

01:34:42.218 --> 01:34:43.636
anybody that has issues with that.

01:34:43.636 --> 01:34:45.012
Maybe try some of that stuff

01:34:45.012 --> 01:34:46.389
because it seems kind of

01:34:46.389 --> 01:34:48.099
nontraditional, but

01:34:48.099 --> 01:34:50.601
it was very valuable

01:34:50.685 --> 01:34:51.352
critiquing the

01:34:51.352 --> 01:34:53.145
substance of Dave's argument,

01:34:53.145 --> 01:34:54.563
saying that they're high level

01:34:54.563 --> 01:34:55.773
or second hand.

01:34:55.773 --> 01:34:57.316
